@startuml
title CADENCE (v2) — weekly loop that closes the line into a cycle

skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #666666

legend top
|<#BAFFC9> | MiniMax M3 (read 100+ issues, cheap) |
|<#FFB3BA> | GLM-5.2 (retro / drift — short, weekly) |
|<#FFD9BA> | DeepSeek V4 Pro (Polish digest to Mateusz) |
endlegend

start
:cron: weekly (or morning_planner / Hermes);
#BAFFC9:Collect state from Linear:\nthroughput, In Progress / In Review,\nblocked, escalated, over-budget, aging WIP;
#FFB3BA:Detect drift:\ntasks without Initiative (no outcome),\nstale needs:* (> X days), old open tasks, WIP overflow;
#BAFFC9:Roadmap refresh: Now / Next / Later\n(update Initiatives);
#FFB3BA:Retro (blameless): went well / badly /\nsurprised + 1-3 action items;
#FFD9BA:Digest (PL) -> @Mateusz:\ntop priorities, blockers, decisions, view links;
if (new input or scope change?) then (yes)
  :feed into PLAN launcher\n(new voice memo / brief);
else (no)
  :wait for next week;
endif
stop

note right
  Read-mostly: does NOT change scope
  without Mateusz (priority changes =
  proposal in the digest).
  This is the 5th element wrapping
  PLAN -> DEV -> REVIEW -> TEST into a loop.
end note
@enduml
